{
    "sections": [
        {
            "title": "Content panels and the basic structure of the application",
            "contents": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "parts": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "When working with the application, your data is organised under a "
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "strong-text",
                            "text": "Project"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "parts": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "Every "
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "strong-text",
                            "text": "Project"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": " contains a "
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "strong-text",
                            "text": "Theme"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": " and several "
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "strong-text",
                            "text": "ContentPanels"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": " These are the main building block for your game world, and govern one area, or category of the assets you want to create. For example, you could have one panel for creating flavour texts for potions, and another for writing books that appear in your game world."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "parts": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "All of the panels inside your project automatically include the theme of your game, and provide it to the AI when you ask it for content."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "icon-tip",
                    "icon": "Bars3Icon",
                    "text": "You can create as many panels as you want. They are organised under the drawer on the left hand side of the screen."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Prompting with IOBoxes",
            "contents": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "parts": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "Under each panel, you can have any number of"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "strong-text",
                            "text": "IOBoxes"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "Each box is responsible for one text output that will be generated by the AI. For example, if your theme was \"sci-fi\", and your category was \"planet\", your prompt could be a short description, such as \"a lizard-aliens' stronghold\"."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "parts": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "The final prompt sent to the AI is constructed by embedding them to the following sentence: \"Write a game flavor text for <prompt> which is a <category> in a <theme> setting\". For the example given above this would yield: \"Write a game flavor text for a lizard-aliens' stronghold which is a planet in a sci-fi setting\"."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "parts": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "The input for each box can be long or detailed, or it could be a single keyword. Each box that you have in a panel can be generated individually from the controls on top of it. You can also generate all boxes in a panel at once, using the"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "strong-text",
                            "text": "Generate all"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "button. Notice that you can edit both the input and ouput of a box by hand!"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "icon-tip",
                    "icon": "LockClosedIcon",
                    "text": "Got a great output you don't want overwritten? You can lock IOBoxes, which prevents them from being edited by the AI generation."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Exporting content",
            "contents": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "parts": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "Once you have generated some outputs from a panel, you can export them to a"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "strong-text",
                            "text": "json"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "or"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "strong-text",
                            "text": "xlsx"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "file. The exported file will contain the category of your panel, and all inputs/outputs currently in that panel."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "icon-tip",
                    "icon": "WindowIcon",
                    "text": "The json format includes more details, such as the parameters that were used to generate the prompts."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Generation parameters and presets",
            "contents": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "parts": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "You can influence the AI generation via"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "strong-text",
                            "text": "Presets"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "and"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "strong-text",
                            "text": "Parameters"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "These can be found by clicking the"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "solid-icon",
                            "icon": "Cog6Tooth"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "icon next to the category of your panel, and selecting"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "strong-text",
                            "text": "Settings"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "This will open a parameter drawer, where you can choose from hand picked items, or set precise values."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "icon-tip",
                    "icon": "InformationCircleIcon",
                    "text": "Don't forget to save your progress! You finetune parameters for each panel seperately if needed."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Multiple panels",
            "contents": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "parts": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "You can add or remove panels from the left-hand drawer. When you give a category to a panel, you can find it with that name from the list of panels."
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}